['About the company

illion is the leading independent provider of trusted data and analytics products and services in Australia and New Zealand. illion leverages its consumer and commercial credit registries to provide end-to-end customer management solutions to clients in the financial services, telecommunications, utilities and government sectors.

We currently have an exciting opportunity for an Organisation and Methods Analyst to join our team. This is a fantastic opportunity for anyone who is looking to increase their skill set and advance their career within a large organisation.


About the role

The key responsibility of the Organisation and Methods Analystis to ensure the team's achievement of performance-based outcomes by providing strategic insight and analysis on a broad range of programs that aim to elevate business performance.


Duties

Work closely and communicate with managers in both NZ and AU to implement and execute strategies to meet KPIs and business goals;
Drive a continuous improvement mindset in the enhancement of internal models, processes and frameworks relating to strategy and deliver a high quality & consistent client experience;
Provide business case assessment, performance tracking, business performance analysis and strategy input;
Deliver on the administrative requirements set forth in each of our clients' contracts;
Analysing and investigating business processes, keeping meticulous documentation and gathering this data into reports for stakeholder.


Skills & Experience

Excellent quantitative and analysis skills;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Strong people leadership skills;
Strong organisational and planning skills;
An understanding of process improvement methodology, dialler technology, Microsoft Excel and statistical reporting software.


Culture

At illion, we are always seeking innovative and forward-thinking individuals to join us on our journey. Our culture is unique. It's fast, results-driven and dynamic. It's certainly not for everyone. But if you thrive in a high performing environment - illion could be for you!


Benefits

Feel good in the workplace - Australia and NZ wide wellness program to foster positive health & wellbeing for all employees.
Social Club - Quarterly calendar of events allowing team member to network and socialized in a fun and relaxed environment
Leadership Development Programs - build your skillset and become an illion future leader


How to Apply

To apply, please click "Apply Now" button and we will be in touch shortly.

To be considered for this position, you must be an Australian/NZ Citizen or have a Permanent Residency visa.']

["Metricon Homes, a leading multi award winning new home builder is committed to recruiting outstanding individuals who share our passion for delivering quality, service and award winning living solutions for Australian families.

We currently have a rare and exciting opportunity for a Business Analyst & Project Delivery to engage with all stakeholders (suppliers and teams) to create an online settlement platform and provide business analytics to stakeholder groups in our Mount Waverley Office.

So if you’re a motivated individual with experience and qualifications aligned to the criteria and a great attitude, we would love to hear from you!
Reporting to the Retail Product Manager, your responsibilities will include:
Research and Content Management;
Research topics and items included in the online settlement pack from building to retail product side;
Literature reviews and desktop research. Structural, building and supplier research. Australian Standards and Building Code research. User research;
Quantitative and qualitative analysis;
Develop and implement a research method to analyse content created on its user friendliness;
Communicate with customers and their data;
Work directly with suppliers to create the database of the online settlement project;
Digital platform delivery and create and implement process of maintenance;
Develop research collection methods;
Data extraction and analysis by liaising with stakeholders;
Maintain and update database management;
Assist in the change & release management process which may include: Project Management, Systems Testing and the Creation of user documentation; and
Create and maintain functional working documents/process maps for key business system processes.
Metricon will offer you:
A competitive salary and salary package opportunities;
Work for Australia's Number 1 New Home Builder 5 Years in a Row;
Genuine career advancement opportunities;
Generous housing discounts on our award winning homes; and
A supportive workplace culture where great work is recognised and rewarded.
The successful candidate will have:
Degree or equivalent in any of the following disciplines: Research, User Experience, Marketing, Communications or Business;
Must have Power BI or similar experience;
Previous experience in a high volume fast paced tech/digital environment;
Previous experience in high volume research (academia preferred);
Able to multi task and operate in a fast paced team environment;
Ability to work flexible hours including weekends, evenings, occasional overtime;
Excellent communicator, by phone, in person and written;
Eager to learn and enjoying staying up to date on products/technology; and
Takes initiative, self-motivated and desire to meet goals.
If you have what it takes to succeed in this role submit your application with your resume and cover letter TODAY!

Metricon Homes complete mandatory national police checks on all successful applicants."]

["Seeking an 'Excel Guru' to add genuine value to a fast-paced environment
Melbourne CBD Fringe
$80k + Superannuation + Genuine Career Opportunties


ABOUT THE COMPANY AND ROLE

Our client is an Australian based management consulting, technology & systems integration company who assist their clients to improve their business strategy, processes, systems and people. They provide services to a wide range of organisations from large multinational to government enterprise and smaller.
Due to extended growth, they now require a driven Junior Analyst to review data and add genuine value to assist making key business decisions:

DUTIES
Support the consulting team with data analysis which assists to identify, develop and execute short and long-term strategies and initiatives for clients;
Be exposed to key internal & external stakeholders, and help to build meaningful long-term relationships with clients;
Align with key stakeholders to help identify opportunities and value-added initiatives;
Operate in a dynamic environment that continually embraces and encourages the implementation of innovative ideas and creates a culture of collaboration and teamwork;
Prepare, communicate and manage the quality checking of documentation and presentations for clients.
SKILLS & EXPERTISE
Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration or related fields;
Previous experience working & analysing complex data sets, with the ability to impact commercial decisions;
Demonstrated strategic and analytical skills with the ability to translate strategy and analysis to a tactical, executable level;
Ability to work effectively in a team-based environment;
Elite Excel skills & MS suite experience required;
Elite presentation and written communication skills;
Strong project management skills with the ability to work on multiple projects and prioritise effectively.
HOW TO APPLY

Click APPLY and attach your current resume. Please be advised our screening process will take approximately 3 to 5 business days from the date this ad was posted. From here, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted."]

